I wanted to dive into real-time web tracking, so I built a Real-Time Gesture & Expression Meme Generator app!
🔗 Check it out here (Live for the next 29 days on a free tier): https://lnkd.in/dsV-CuX9

How it works:
                Using Google Media Pipe, the app analyzes your webcam stream in real-time to read complex facial structures and hand shapes. Instead of using standard coordinate tracking, it evaluates Finger State Vectors to determine if fingers are open or closed.
It maps your expressions and movements directly to pop-culture templates side-by-side.

The Experience:
                 As a beginner, this was an incredible learning experience. I built this with the help of AI pair-programming, which helped me figure out complex canvas math (like un-mirroring text transformations) and handling real-time data loops.
It’s definitely not flawless or 100% perfect, but it was a massive playground for learning how to bridge frontend UI with complex computer vision libraries.

